Black-green smudges at 98, 115-120, 137-138 cm and a diagonal black-green horizon from 62-68 cm.  Moderate to heavy burrowing apparent in Sections 1-2 due to the presence of ?Mn-oxide layers. Burrowing of darker oxides lends Section 1 a mottled appearance.

Black-green smudges at 53.5 and 79 cm.  Green horizon at 102 cm with dispersed green flecks below (102-150cm, continued to the top of Section 3, 9cm). Mottled, darker ?Mn-oxide interval ends at  102 cm after which obvious burrow disappear (i.e., bioturbation intensity is heavy from 102-150 cm).

The Munsell listed is the dominant color (present from 53-138 cm). From 53-81 cm and 104-138 cm the brown interval is darker and more homogenous as compared to 81-104 cm (lighter with some mottling).  From 0-53 cm a secondary color (blue-greener, 10GY 5/1) dominates; bioturbation is heavy, and rare green flecks are present throughout (most green flecks occur from 0-9 cm). The secondary color (10GY 5/1 again dominates from 138-150cm, with coffee colored mottling from bioturbation of the overlying browner interval.

The Munsell color listed is the dominant color from 19-50 cm, with coffee-color mottling due to bioturbation with surrounding browner intervals.  A secondary, browner interval is present from 0-19 cm and a relatively green horizon at 39 cm. A sharp diagonal contact between relatively blue grey and relatively brown sediments is present at 50 cm (with relatively brown underlying relatively blue).
This interval (50-122cm) is characterized by silty clay with quartz and ends with a sharp diagonal contact at 122 cm.

Centimeter to decimeter scale beds (browner layers thicker than medium and light blue layers) from 122-143 cm.  Relatively abrupt horizontal contact at 143 cm with a light blue-grey interval, lightly mottled interval from 143-150.5 cm.
